Johnny Kaye wants to book his six female impersonators into some Reno night club. They're marking time in Kansas City, awaiting reply.

"sensational toe-dancer now in his third week in Karyl Norman's male revue . . . featured to accompany the starred songs of Spanish-singing Billy Herrero." "One of Johnson's outstanding numbers is a swing version of the ever-popular 'Song of India,' done with the clinking finger-cymbals so typical of this British protectorate of the Orient."
